The convolution theorem for the discrete-time Fourier transform (DTFT) indicates that a convolution of two sequences can be obtained as the inverse transform of the product of the individual transforms. An important simplification occurs when one of sequences is N-periodic, denoted here by formula_66 because formula_67 is non-zero at only discrete frequencies (see ), and therefore so is its product with the continuous function formula_68  That leads to a considerable simplification of the inverse transform.

